    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1986-11-26T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1986-11-26T00:00:00-05:00" n="165"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d165">
                <head>165. Memorandum From <persName corresp="#p_BLF_1">Linton Brooks</persName> and
                        <persName corresp="#p_LR_2">Robert Linhard</persName> of the National
                    Security Council Staff to the President’s Assistant for National Security
                    Affairs (<persName corresp="#p_PJM_1">Poindexter</persName>)<note n="1"
                        type="source" xml:id="d165fn1">Source: National Security Council, National
                        Security Council Institutional Files, Box SR–111, <gloss target="#t_NSPG_1"
                            >NSPG</gloss> 0140, 11/25/1986. Secret. Sent for action. A copy was sent
                        to <persName corresp="#p_CW_1">Cockell</persName>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1986-11-26">November 26, 1986</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <list type="subject">
                    <head>SUBJECT</head>
                    <item>131st Bomber Game Plan</item>
                </list>
                <p>Attached at <hi rend="italic">Tab I</hi>
                    <note n="2" xml:id="d165fn2">Printed as <ref target="#d166">Document
                        166</ref>.</note> is a memorandum to the President seeking his approval,
                    based on yesterday’s <gloss target="#t_NSPG_1">NSPG</gloss>,<note n="3"
                        xml:id="d165fn3">See <ref target="#d164">Document 164</ref>.</note> to
                    proceed with the deployment of the 131st bomber and providing a game plan for
                    Congressional and Allied notification. The package includes talking points we
                    will use with Congress and a suggested announcement <gloss target="#t_DOD_1"
                        >DOD</gloss> might make on Friday.<note n="4" xml:id="d165fn4">November 28.
                        Tabs A and B are printed as the attachments to <ref target="#d166">Document
                            166</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <p>To support <persName corresp="#p_AD_1">Dave Abshire</persName>’s desire to get
                    the 131st bomber behind us as soon as possible, Congressional notification needs
                    to be made today. <persName corresp="#p_SR_1">Ron Sable</persName> is poised to
                    begin that process as soon as we have Presidential approval. You should note,
                    however, that the bomber will not actually return to its operations base until
                    after several days of testing. We believe we should declare it operational now
                    to avoid the conflict with the scheduled <gloss target="#t_NATO_1">NATO</gloss>
                    meetings.</p>
                <p rend="sectiontitleital">Recommendation</p>
                <p>That you sign the memorandum to the President at <hi rend="italic">Tab
                        I</hi>.<note n="5" xml:id="d165fn5">
                        <persName corresp="#p_KAGA_1">Keel</persName> approved the
                        recommendation.</note>
                </p>
                <p>
                    <persName corresp="#p_SR_1">Ron Sable</persName>, <persName corresp="#p_MD_1"
                        >Don Mahley</persName>, <persName corresp="#p_SSR_1">Steve
                        Steiner</persName> and <persName corresp="#p_TW_1">Will Tobey</persName>
                        concur.<note n="6" xml:id="d165fn6">
                        <persName corresp="#p_BLF_1">Brooks</persName> concurred on behalf of
                            <persName corresp="#p_SR_1">Sable</persName>, <persName
                            corresp="#p_MD_1">Mahley</persName>, <persName corresp="#p_SSR_1"
                            >Steiner</persName>, and <persName corresp="#p_TW_1"
                        >Tobey</persName>.</note>
                    <persName corresp="#p_KS_1">Sven Kraemer</persName> is on travel.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
